      <h2>How to Choose the Right Ion Bar</h2>
      <p>Five factors determine the correct static eliminator for a given application:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Coverage length</strong> — select a bar length that matches or slightly exceeds substrate width (150–1,500mm standard; custom lengths available)</li>
        <li><strong>Working distance</strong> — most units operate at 25–300mm; use DC pulsed type within 50–100mm for residual charge below ±20V</li>
        <li><strong>Line speed</strong> — high-speed lines need multiple bars in series or closer mounting to maintain low residual charge</li>
        <li><strong>AC vs. DC</strong> — AC for general use; DC pulsed or intelligent type for display and semiconductor applications</li>
        <li><strong>Environment</strong> — cleanrooms require sealed housings; dusty environments require accessible needle arrays for cleaning</li>
      </ol>

